 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../212/48212.xml">
ice cream</link> made with layers of different colors and flavors, usually containing candied <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../843/10843.xml">
fruits</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../647/251647.xml">
nuts</link>. Typically it is of three flavors, with a fruit/nut layer between them. The ice cream layers are often mixed with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../652/4744652.xml">
whipped cream</link>. <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../089/7089.xml">
Chocolate</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../584/40584.xml">
pistachio</link> are the typical flavors of the ice cream layers, and the fruit/nut layer often contains <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../773/54773.xml">
cherry</link> bits -- causing the traditional red/pink, brown, and green color combination.
